{"id": "duc04-testb-18:9#28", "contents": "The investigation into President Clinton's actions began with a land deal in Arkansas in 1978 and eventually expanded to include his affair with a White House intern, thanks to the efforts of independent counsel Kenneth Starr. Despite the immense public interest in the scandal, polls have consistently shown that the public opposes impeachment and wants the inquiry to end. A recent CBS News Poll found that only 38 percent of respondents wanted their representative to vote for impeachment, while 58 percent opposed it. The conflict now enters uncharted territory, as the Nixon resignation and the Johnson trial occurred under different circumstances."}
